content: Physics Run plan for 1010719, MP 287 Asdex H-mode similarity experiment

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: Goal: To make high density, high power EDA H-modes in a shape identical to

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: that in ASDEX-Upgrade 'Type II ELM' discharges. This regime,

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: which was only recently obtained on AUG, appears rather similar to that

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: obtained on C-Mod when power is increased into EDA H-modes. At reduced powers,

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: AUG sometimes sees a 'quasi-coherent' mode. We would like to see if the same

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: behaviour is observed on the two machines with the same dimensionless

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: parameters. We will obtain edge profiles both at threshold and in the steady

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: H-mode period. AUG will then try to match the

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: dimensionless parameters (nu*,beta, rho*) of these discharges.

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: 1) Obtain suitable shape, plasma parameters. Start with shape from shot

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: 1010605016. Raise Ip to 1.0 MA, keep Bt at 5.3 T. L-mode nel=1.1e20 m-2.

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: Once plasma is obtained, adjust shape to get a better match to AUG pulse 14265.

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: This will involve increasing the inner gap and the radius of the x-point.

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: RF should use these shots (3-4?) to tune and condition;

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: For the last shot we would like a power ramp up to >~2 MW to get the

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: threshold power, and both L and H-mode tunes.

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: 2) High power EDAs. Use square wave RF pulse at Ptot=2.5 MW using D and E at

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: 80 MHz (more if we can get it). Measure pedestals, and fluctuations.

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: Tune J-port at low power on these.

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: 3) Add power from J-port (70 MHz), at maximum available power. This will be

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: off-axis, which is non-optimal, but should help to raise pedestal temperature.

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: 4) Increase density. A dimensionless match to the best AUG 'grassy ELM' shots

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: would correspond to a line integrated density of 4.7e20, higher than our usual

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: range. Increase starting density, and probably puff gas into EDA, to see how

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: high we can get and still maintain a decent, steady H-mode (and couple enough

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: power). ECE will probably be cut off, so good ETS data are essential.

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: Again, use max available power without and with J-port.

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: 4) Once the 'high density' H-mode has been characterized, use a slow power

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: ramp to determine the corresponding threshold power and edge parameters.

content: We had limited success with this run, primarily due to poor machine conditions.

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: This was probably a result of the recent vent, combined with the fact that we

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: were running non-standard shapes, and thus putting power on different vessel

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: surfaces. This led to impurity injections and, most critically, to a high

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: hydrogen fraction (up to 20%) which limited the RF power absorption; H/D

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: typically increases during each discharge, with Pabs decreasing.

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: The shape development part of the run went quite smoothly, and we

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: did get shots which were a very close match to ASDEX Upgrade shapes (see

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: physics operator summary for details of changes made). These had elongation

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: close to our vertical stability limits (k~1.73), and were close to double null,

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: which may have caused some interaction with upper vessel surfaces, and possibly

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: also increased H-mode thresholds. The last AUG shaped shot, 1010719020, is a

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: J-port was not available for the run after all, so we ran with typically 2.3

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: MW at 80 MHz from D and E port antennas. However, the low absorption means

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: that the effective power was actually much lower, especially late in the pulse.

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: We were unable to get any H-modes which had a steady, EDA character. Many were

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: ELM-free, with strongly increasing impurities. (eg. shot 2, 14). Others, with

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: lower power and higher radiation, had periodic behaviour typical of Type III

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: ELMs; the pedestal was very cold (eg. shots 5,13). On shots 9 and 11 we ramped

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: the RF up slowly to get threshold data, and found it was over the 2.3 MW

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: injected); this is very high for these C-Mod conditions. Making the discharge

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: more 'single null' had little effect (shot 12). Lowering the target density

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: from nel= 0.9 to 0.7e20 m-2, while it had minimal effect on nebar at the RF

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: onset (1.35-1.4e20m-3 in both cases), resulted in much lower neutral pressure

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: anda threshold of Prf=1.13 MW (shot 13). This may be a good point for threshold

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: comparison, though it was rather early in the ramp. Shot 14 had full RF power

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: at this density, and resulted in ELM-free H-modes.

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: In an attempts to favour the EDA regime, Ip was lowered from 1.0 to 0.9 MA from

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: shot 15 on. This raised q95 to 4.2. The rates of density rise did decrease

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: slightly, though not an obvious EDA regime. Shot 16 had hints of a weak

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: mode on PCI. Shot 17 was colder and more ELMy. From shot 19 Bt was raised

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: from 5.3 T to 5.6 T, raising q95 still further and a better match to the AUG

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: target. This proved more difficult for the RF to match, for reasons not well

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: understood at least by me, and power was not as steady as the rest of the day.

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: The density did appear to be getting more steady, and QC modes characteristic

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: of EDA were seen on PCI. Shot 21, about 0.75-0.8 secs, may be a good time for

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: pedestal analysis. For shot 22, we went back to a standard shape, 800 kA shot

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: to check we could get EDA there. We did, but it quickly cooled and reverted to

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: Type III ELMs as H/D rose.

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: In summary, as expected, it was more difficult to get steady H-modes in the

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: lower triangularity ASDEX-Upgrade shape. However, the poor machine conditions

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: and low absorbed power undoubtedly were a major impediment, and there were

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: indications we were getting close. There was insufficient power to try raising

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: the density. Since the discharge development has been successfully completed,

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: we would very much like to revisit this experiment on a day with better vessel

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: conditions and all three RF antennas available.

content: Shapes that are an excellent match to the scaled AUG shape were

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: obtained (e.g. 21) and many were run. A comparison plot is in

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: user10:[hutch.ps]aug_match.ps. They are close to double null;

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: although a range of three sseps was run without obvious effect on the

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: plasma character. No solid EDA H-modes were obtained. The H/D was high

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: and rose strongly with RF in the early part of the day. Later on, the

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: rises seemed less significant, but in all cases the H/D was above 10%

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: during much of the RF pulse. Heating was clearly inefficient in many

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: cases. In some others heating was ok even at high H/D.

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: The early part of the day was plagued with injections. Many appeared

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: to be caused by visible sparks on the upper left corner of D-antenna.

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: Some others were not RF induced. As the day wore on, these problems

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: were less severe, and the plasma ran reasonably reliably.

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: These shapes are fairly close to stability limits. One or two VDEs were

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: experienced. The chopper V was set to 150 to 200 instead of the usual 0

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: to lower the operating average current to a position closer to the center

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: of its range. This adjustment seemed to be a significant improvement in

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: that it allowed operation with an elongation that gave rise to noisy chopper

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: behaviour without leading to saturations and subsequent VDE.

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: A manual gas puff during the RF did not significantly improve the

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: operation, but also did not seem to give much impact on the RF coupling

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: despite a x2 rise in main chamber neutral pressure.

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: It appears to be confirmed that the lower triangularity that is needed to

tag: html body text table tbody tr td small span
content: match AUG makes it harder to get into EDA. The high H level was also
